</div>
<p><strong>Welcome to MarkThompsonAstronomy.Com</strong> the site for all your astronomy information.   In these pages, you will find everything the amateur astronomer needs from advice in getting started all the way to advanced observing techniques and weather forecasts designed by an astronomer, for the astronomer.</p>
<div class="margtb20">
<hr class="margtb20" />
<div class="floatl w140px margr20"><img src="http://www.markthompsonastronomy.com/wp-content/uploads/red_torch.jpg" alt="" title="Red Torch" width="140" height="105" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-88" /></div>
<div class="floatl w410px">
<h2 class="marg0"><a href="/practical-astronomy/">Practical Astronomy</a></h2>
<p class="marg0">Like most hobbies, getting started in astronomy can be quite challenging.  From learning your way around the sky to the first telescope  purchase, thereâ€™s lots to learn. In these pages you will find everything you need to know to get started in astronomy and a little bit more.</p>
</div>
<div class="clear"></div>
<hr class="margtb20" />
<div class="floatl w140px margr20"><img src="http://www.markthompsonastronomy.com/wp-content/uploads/clouds.jpg" alt="" title="Clouds" width="140" height="105" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-88" /></div>
<div class="floatl w410px">
<h2 class="marg0"><a href="/weather-forecasting/">Astronomy Weather Forecasts</a></h2>
<p class="marg0">The Astronomy Weather Forecasts are based on a ground breaking new forecast model to bring you a forecast designed especially for the astronomer.  They are uniquely easy to read and will tell you just what you need to know.</p>
</div>
<div class="clear"></div>
<hr class="margtb20" />
<div class="floatl w140px margr20"><img src="http://www.markthompsonastronomy.com/wp-content/uploads/star-clusters.jpg" alt="" title="Star Clusters" width="140" height="105" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-88" /></div>
<div class="floatl w410px">
<h2 class="marg0"><a href="/introducing-the-universe/">Introducing the Universe</a></h2>
<p class="marg0">When you look at the night sky, all you can see are stars, right? Wrong.  There&#8217;s a wealth of other objects in the Universe to see.  Understanding their nature will enhance your enjoyment of astronomy.  In this section you will find descriptions of the objects and processes taking place in the Universe.</p>
</div>
<div class="clear"></div>
<hr class="margtb20" />
<div class="floatl w140px margr20"><img src="http://www.markthompsonastronomy.com/wp-content/uploads/TEMP-stars.jpg" alt="" title="TEMP-stars" width="140" height="105" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-88" /></div>
<div class="floatl w410px">
<h2 class="marg0"><a href="/blog/">Blog</a></h2>
<p class="marg0">Astronomy is a fast moving subject.  New worlds are discovered, old theories proved wrong and strange new processes uncovered at an alarming rate.  Keep checking back to my blog to keep up to date with all things happening in the world of astronomy. </p>
</div>
<div class="clear"></div>
<hr class="margtb20" /></div>

				
